  "body": "my geth is the latest version\r\nThe server is ubunt 8v 21g hard disk 1.5T bandwidth peak 25G\r\nStart command geth --http --ws --maxpeers 35 --rpc.txfeecap 0\r\n\r\nWhat makes me sad is that every half month or more he will force quit and I have no way of knowing what's going on in my server and what can be avoided\r\nThe log looks normal. After each forced exit, it needs to synchronize about 20,000 blocks. Is there any way to avoid it?\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [03-28|05:05:55.958] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1     txs=10        mgas=0.983   elapsed=26.435ms    mgasps=37.177   number=14,470,573 hash=0809df..1379ae dirty=1010.64MiB\r\nINFO [03-28|05:05:55.960] Unindexed transactions                   blocks=1     txs=152       tail=12,120,574 elapsed=1.917ms\r\nINFO [03-28|05:06:09.556] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1     txs=230       mgas=16.121  elapsed=106.680ms   mgasps=151.112  number=14,470,574 hash=de2482..3c4c7d dirty=1009.87MiB\r\nINFO [03-28|05:06:09.559] Unindexed transactions                   blocks=1     txs=131       tail=12,120,575 elapsed=2.321ms\r\n```",
